<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="434" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of Malcolm “Chip” Jones for his contributions to cycad conservation and horticulture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[710,1079,222,249]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vazquezi" subGenus="Vovidesa">
<emphasis box="[710,845,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Ceratophila</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[864,964,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Vovidesa</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[983,1079,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">vazquezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which, based on the principal component analysis (
<figureCitation box="[386,450,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1116,1140]" captionTargetBox="[239,1350,517,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-155@2.[216,1370,489,1092]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Scatter plot score derived from the functions produced by stepwise discriminant analysis of 3 anatomical characters from five populations of Ceratophila: A: males; B: females. PC1 is related to the two characters of: ratio of pronotal length to pronotal width (PL/PW) and ratio of pronotal length to elytra length (PL/EL). PC2 is related to the character: ratio of head width to ventral interocular distance (HW/VI)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6623169" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6623169/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), appears widely distributed in central 
<collectingRegion box="[882,981,259,285]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1034,1128,258,284]" country="Mexico" name="Hidalgo" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Hidalgo</collectingRegion>
. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Gomez Dominguez" authorityYear="2022" box="[1198,1390,258,285]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chipjonesi" subGenus="Vovidesa">
<emphasis box="[1198,1224,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1239,1260,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">V.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1275,1390,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">chipjonesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,327,294,321]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vazquezi" subGenus="Vovidesa">
<emphasis box="[151,177,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[193,215,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">V.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[231,327,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">vazquezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share the diagnostic characters of males with meso- and metatibia with a distinct medial subapical emargination and mentum with long setae projecting laterally. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Gomez Dominguez" authorityYear="2022" box="[871,1179,330,357]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chipjonesi" subGenus="Vovidesa">
<emphasis box="[871,1006,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Ceratophila</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1025,1046,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">V.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1064,1179,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">chipjonesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs mainly in possessing a longer, narrower pronotum (see results of PCA above). On the 
<specimenCount box="[969,1071,366,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
cone of 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1437,366,393]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratozamia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="santillanii">
<emphasis box="[1170,1437,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="434">Ceratozamia santillanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sampled for this paper, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Gomez Dominguez" authorityYear="2022" box="[413,606,402,429]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Ceratophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="6" pageNumber="434" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chipjonesi" subGenus="Vovidesa">
